  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0dd8\u0dc2\u0dd2 \u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2\u0dab \u0db8\u0dab\u0dca\u0da9\u0dbd\u0dba\u0da7 \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1 163\u0d9a \u0db4\u0dcf\u0da9\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "163 million loss to Agriculture Insurance Board",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It is said that due to the cancellation of the insurance agreement made by the Agriculture and Rural Insurance Board with the Insurance Trust Fund, the Agriculture Board has incurred a loss of 163.6 million rupees.",
        "This is stated in the annual audit report issued by the National Audit Office for the year 2020 regarding the Agricultural and Agricultural Insurance Scheme.",
        "According to the underwriting agreement with the insurance trust fund, a sum of 312 million rupees should have been obtained to pay the first 10,000 rupees of the total compensation value that could be recorded for one farmer in the yala season of 2019.",
        "But the audit has revealed that the Agriculture Board has incurred a loss of 163.6 million rupees because the Agriculture Board canceled the agreement and received an amount of 148.3 million rupees in the year 2020 instead of receiving the outstanding amount.",
        "The management of the Agriculture Board has informed the audit that this amount has not been received by the Agriculture Board because the insurance cover was not implemented."
      ],
